1
00:00:02,210 --> 00:00:06,298
SISKO:
<i>Captain's Personal Log,</i>
<i>Stardate 51247.5.</i>

2
00:00:06,340 --> 00:00:09,551
<i>It's been a week since</i>
<i>our return to Deep Space 9,</i>

3
00:00:09,593 --> 00:00:12,137
<i>but the mood</i>
<i>of celebration continues.</i>

4
00:00:12,179 --> 00:00:14,264
<i>We're still at war,</i>
<i>and the station's</i>

5
00:00:14,306 --> 00:00:16,308
<i>been designated headquarters</i>
<i>for the Ninth Fleet.</i>

6
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:18,435
<i>That, plus</i>
<i>our strategic position</i>

7
00:00:18,477 --> 00:00:20,688
<i>guarding the wormhole,</i>
<i>makes DS9</i>

8
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:22,439
<i>one of the most</i>
<i>tempting targets</i>

9
00:00:22,481 --> 00:00:24,065
<i>in the entire quadrant.</i>

10
00:00:24,107 --> 00:00:28,069
<i>But for now, at least,</i>
<i>the war seems very far away.</i>

11
00:00:34,535 --> 00:00:35,494
Morning.
Good morning.

12
00:00:35,536 --> 00:00:37,329
Good morning.

13
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:38,747
Morning, Major.

14
00:00:38,789 --> 00:00:40,541
Good morning, Captain.

15
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:42,250
Do you know
how much I missed

16
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,669
hearing you say that?

17
00:00:43,711 --> 00:00:45,796
Do you know how much
I hated saying

18
00:00:45,838 --> 00:00:46,881
"Good morning, Dukat"?

19
00:00:46,922 --> 00:00:47,882
I can imagine.

20
00:00:47,923 --> 00:00:49,299
What's on the agenda?

21
00:00:49,341 --> 00:00:52,177
Uh, USS<i> Potemkin</i>
has completed her repairs

22
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,262
and is rejoining the fleet
later today.

23
00:00:54,304 --> 00:00:56,015
<i>Exeter, Sutherland</i>
and<i> Agaki</i>

24
00:00:56,056 --> 00:00:57,933
have submitted
resupply requests

25
00:00:57,975 --> 00:00:59,935
and there are
about 1,000 messages

26
00:00:59,977 --> 00:01:01,353
from Starfleet Command

27
00:01:01,395 --> 00:01:03,355
awaiting your "eyes-only"
attention.

28
00:01:03,397 --> 00:01:04,773
Anything else?

29
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:06,901
General Martok is waiting
in your office.

30
00:01:06,942 --> 00:01:08,861
Oh, I'll start
with the General.

31
00:01:08,903 --> 00:01:10,278
I thought you would.

32
00:01:12,531 --> 00:01:15,242
Have I mentioned
that it's good to be home?

33
00:01:16,618 --> 00:01:18,328
Once or twice.

34
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:22,082
All right.

35
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:28,087
You knew about this,
didn't you?

36
00:01:28,129 --> 00:01:29,798
Oh, I had a pretty good idea.

37
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:32,760
And you did nothing to stop it.

38
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:34,344
No.

39
00:01:34,386 --> 00:01:37,180
In fact, I recommended you
for the position myself.

40
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:39,516
Allow me to offer
my congratulations

41
00:01:39,558 --> 00:01:41,351
to the new
Supreme Commander

42
00:01:41,393 --> 00:01:42,937
of the Ninth Fleet.

43
00:01:44,271 --> 00:01:46,565
Do you have any idea
how much paperwork

44
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:48,859
a Supreme Commander
has to do?

45
00:01:48,901 --> 00:01:49,860
You're welcome.

46
00:01:49,902 --> 00:01:52,071
(<i> growls</i> )

47
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:53,948
May I arrange quarters
for you on the station?

48
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:57,534
No, I'll keep my flag
aboard the<i> Rotarran.</i>

49
00:01:57,576 --> 00:02:01,246
It may be cramped
but at least I'll feel
like I'm still in the war.

50
00:02:01,288 --> 00:02:04,291
By the way, I'd like Worf
to continue functioning

51
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:06,167
as my principal
Intelligence Officer.

52
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:08,211
I don't see any problem
with that.

53
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:11,214
He's the only officer I know
who can never get enough work.

54
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,341
(<i> cackles</i> )

55
00:02:13,383 --> 00:02:14,885
Well, at least if he's busy

56
00:02:14,927 --> 00:02:18,263
he'll stop going on
about this wedding of his.

57
00:02:19,514 --> 00:02:21,850
Oh, there were times
aboard the<i> Rotarran</i>

58
00:02:21,892 --> 00:02:23,644
he nearly drove me mad.

59
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:26,855
Until his son arrived,
it was all he could talk about.

60
00:02:26,897 --> 00:02:29,733
Then Alexander became
all he could talk about.

61
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:33,403
The man is nothing
if not single-minded.

62
00:02:33,445 --> 00:02:35,238
I haven't met Worf's son yet.

63
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,240
What's he like?

64
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:38,951
He's a fine boy...

65
00:02:38,993 --> 00:02:41,620
dedicated, eager.

66
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:44,456
He has the heart
of his father

67
00:02:44,498 --> 00:02:47,918
but he's not the best
soldier I've ever seen.

68
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,545
But when he ordered me
to bring the system
back online,

69
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:51,880
I thought he was still talking

70
00:02:51,922 --> 00:02:54,549
about the hydro-static
system, so...

71
00:02:54,591 --> 00:02:55,759
You didn't
engage the pumps

72
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:57,427
while the check valves
were open.

73
00:02:57,469 --> 00:02:58,762
He did.

74
00:02:58,804 --> 00:03:00,681
I flooded
the entire deck

75
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:02,557
with super-heated
hydraulic fluid.

76
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,977
It took me three days
to clean it up

77
00:03:05,019 --> 00:03:07,729
but, I swear, it still smells
like burnt dog hair in there.

78
00:03:07,771 --> 00:03:11,025
Oh! Remind me to keep you away
from the<i> Defiant.</i>
You're a menace.

79
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:14,235
The<i> Rotarran's</i> crew
actually thinks of me
as a good luck charm.

80
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:19,533
You know, the more mistakes
<i>I</i> make, the safer<i> they</i> feel.

81
00:03:19,574 --> 00:03:22,119
I hope the<i> Ya'Vang's crew</i>
feels the same way.

82
00:03:22,161 --> 00:03:23,787
The<i> Ya'Vang?</i>

83
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:26,915
I got new orders this morning.

84
00:03:26,957 --> 00:03:29,793
The battle cruiser<i> Ya'Vang</i>
took heavy losses

85
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:31,503
in their last engagement

86
00:03:31,545 --> 00:03:33,922
so most of the<i> Rotarran's crew</i>
are being transferred there

87
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:36,675
at the end of the week,
including me.

88
00:03:38,677 --> 00:03:41,180
Uh, more bloodwine?

89
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:42,389
Why not?

90
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,391
No. Not for me.

91
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,811
Handsome young man.

92
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:50,105
He must get his
looks from his
mother's side.

93
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,606
What do you want?

94
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:55,152
Have you had a chance
to reconsider my offer?

95
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:58,155
We are not getting
married in this bar.

96
00:03:58,197 --> 00:04:00,782
The ceremony
will take place
on the Klingon homeworld

97
00:04:00,824 --> 00:04:02,034
after the war.

98
00:04:02,076 --> 00:04:05,204
Worf, let's do it here,
this week

99
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:06,538
before Alexander leaves.

100
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:07,831
QUARK:
Perfect.

101
00:04:07,873 --> 00:04:09,124
I'll handle
all the arrangements.

102
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:11,919
Wait. I thought
we had agreed.

103
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,171
We did, but I would hate
for Alexander

104
00:04:14,213 --> 00:04:15,422
to miss
his father's wedding.

105
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:18,092
It would mean so much to him.

106
00:04:19,051 --> 00:04:22,012
And besides,
it may be a long time

107
00:04:22,054 --> 00:04:24,098
before you see him again.

108
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,231
What's going on?

109
00:04:35,192 --> 00:04:37,069
Our wedding plans
have changed.

110
00:04:37,111 --> 00:04:40,280
We are getting
married here
on Deep Space 9

111
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:43,909
and I would like you
to be my<i> Tawi'Yan.</i>

112
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:48,872
"Sword-bearer."

113
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:51,499
It's sort of like
a best man.

114
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:53,668
Me?

115
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:55,003
Really?

116
00:04:55,045 --> 00:04:55,879
Oh, that's great!

117
00:04:55,921 --> 00:04:57,714
(<i> yelping</i> )

118
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:02,094
I'll put that
on your tab.

119
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:04,299
DAX:
It doesn't
leave much time

120
00:07:04,341 --> 00:07:05,884
to make
all the arrangements

121
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:07,969
but fortunately, there isn't
that much left to do.

122
00:07:08,011 --> 00:07:09,846
Worf's been planning
the ceremony

123
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:11,390
for the last three months.

124
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:13,267
He has everything
figured out

125
00:07:13,308 --> 00:07:15,435
right down
to the color of my shoes.

126
00:07:15,476 --> 00:07:18,397
No offense, Jadzia,
but it seems like this
wedding's

127
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:20,023
all about what Worf wants.

128
00:07:20,065 --> 00:07:22,859
Uh, Habitat Ring,
Section 51 Gamma.

129
00:07:22,901 --> 00:07:24,819
What about you?

130
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:27,322
A traditional Klingon wedding
with all the trimmings

131
00:07:27,364 --> 00:07:30,450
is something Worf's
been thinking about
since he was a boy.

132
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:33,120
It probably has something
to do with being raised

133
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:34,704
by human parents.

134
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,915
In any case, when it comes
to Klingon tradition,

135
00:07:36,957 --> 00:07:38,125
Worf is very sentimental.

136
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,667
Worf?

137
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:41,669
All men are sentimental.

138
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,299
They just cover it up with
scowls and clenched jaws.

139
00:07:45,340 --> 00:07:50,011
There are times when Worf
literally gets misty-eyed

140
00:07:50,053 --> 00:07:52,347
talking about
Klingon rituals.

141
00:07:53,432 --> 00:07:55,392
So, uh, that's
why you're letting him

142
00:07:55,434 --> 00:07:57,018
make the plans
for the wedding?

143
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:59,146
Mostly, but
the truth is

144
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:00,647
I've already
been through five

145
00:08:00,688 --> 00:08:01,773
Trill ceremonies--

146
00:08:01,815 --> 00:08:03,442
three as a bride,
two as a groom,

147
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:04,692
and I'm a little bored with it.

148
00:08:04,734 --> 00:08:05,944
Is it my imagination

149
00:08:05,986 --> 00:08:07,821
or did Odo just
try and avoid us?

150
00:08:07,862 --> 00:08:09,239
I didn't notice.

151
00:08:09,781 --> 00:08:10,991
(<i> sighs</i> )

152
00:08:11,032 --> 00:08:12,617
We've been avoiding
each other

153
00:08:12,659 --> 00:08:14,786
ever since the Dominion
left the station.

154
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:16,413
I think we're both
afraid of talking

155
00:08:16,455 --> 00:08:18,415
about what happened
during the occupation.

156
00:08:18,457 --> 00:08:20,917
What do you mean?

157
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:23,337
Oh, to tell you the truth,

158
00:08:23,378 --> 00:08:26,423
it's nothing I want to talk
about right now either.

159
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:30,969
Thank you for coming.

160
00:08:31,011 --> 00:08:32,929
As you probably know by now,

161
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:35,932
Jadzia and I will be married
here on the station
in six days.

162
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:37,517
There's nothing
more romantic

163
00:08:37,558 --> 00:08:39,936
than a wedding on
DS9 in springtime.

164
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:41,688
When the neutrinos
are in bloom.

165
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:44,983
By tradition,
the Klingon man spends

166
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:46,360
the four nights
before his wedding

167
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:48,695
on a mental
and spiritual journey.

168
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:51,906
It is called<i> Kal'Hyah,</i>
"The Path of Clarity"

169
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:56,119
<i>and</i> he is accompanied
by his closest male friends.

170
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:58,663
You cannot imagine
the experience that awaits us--

171
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:03,251
four long nights filled
with song and fellowship.

172
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:05,628
A time of unbridled pleasures.

173
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:08,589
Are we talking
about a bachelor party here?

174
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:11,009
It is a similar ritual.

175
00:09:11,051 --> 00:09:12,719
Sounds good to me.

176
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,221
Me, too.

177
00:09:14,262 --> 00:09:15,889
Count me in.

178
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,391
We will meet
in the holosuite

179
00:09:17,432 --> 00:09:19,100
tomorrow night
at 2100 hours.

180
00:09:19,142 --> 00:09:21,395
MARTOK:
I advise you all
to get plenty of rest.

181
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:23,646
Four nights
at a Klingon bachelor party.

182
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:25,273
Just think of
the possibilities.

183
00:09:25,315 --> 00:09:26,483
Thank God
Keiko's not here.

184
00:09:26,525 --> 00:09:27,859
I wonder what Dax
will be doing

185
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:30,028
while we're traveling
down<i> Kal'Hyah.</i>

186
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:32,572
She will be taking
a different journey...

187
00:09:32,613 --> 00:09:34,908
with my wife.

188
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,618
Your wife?

189
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:44,000
By marrying Worf,

190
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:46,169
Dax will be joining
the House of Martok.

191
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:48,004
Since the mistress
of a great House

192
00:09:48,046 --> 00:09:49,630
must approve all marriages,

193
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:51,132
Sirella will spend
the next four days

194
00:09:51,174 --> 00:09:52,967
evaluating Jadzia.

195
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:02,852
My lady.

196
00:10:02,894 --> 00:10:05,730
You've put on weight...

197
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:08,149
and your hair is going gray.

198
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:14,030
My deterioration
is proceeding apace.

199
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:17,158
I thought you would be
in your grave by now.

200
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,326
(<i> chuckling</i> )

201
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:20,287
I shall endeavor to die--

202
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:22,080
this year, if possible.

203
00:10:22,122 --> 00:10:24,999
Allow me to present
Captain Benjamin Sisko,

204
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:26,960
Commander of Deep Space 9.

205
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:28,962
Captain, may I present

206
00:10:29,003 --> 00:10:31,881
the mistress of the House
of Martok, my wife

207
00:10:31,923 --> 00:10:33,800
and the mother
of my children...

208
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:36,344
Sirella, daughter of Linkasa.

209
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,139
Welcome to
Deep Space 9.

210
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,308
Thank you, Captain.

211
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:42,725
Where is she?

212
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:45,395
Jadzia's quarters
are in the Habitat Ring,

213
00:10:45,437 --> 00:10:48,231
Section... 25 Alpha.

214
00:10:48,273 --> 00:10:49,483
Shall I escort you?

215
00:10:49,524 --> 00:10:51,025
It's quite far away.

216
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,777
I'll find my way.

217
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,740
If you'll excuse me.

218
00:11:01,495 --> 00:11:04,498
Magnificent, isn't she?

219
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:16,384
Are those real
<i>var'Hama</i> candles?

220
00:11:16,426 --> 00:11:18,595
Yes, Worf,
I traveled to Kronos.

221
00:11:18,637 --> 00:11:21,680
I captured three<i> targs</i>
in the Hamar mountains,

222
00:11:21,722 --> 00:11:23,141
made the ritual
sacrifice at dawn,

223
00:11:23,183 --> 00:11:25,226
came back
to the station,

224
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:27,437
asked Quark to boil their
shoulders into tallow.

225
00:11:27,479 --> 00:11:30,940
Then, I spent two days
molding them into candles

226
00:11:30,982 --> 00:11:32,066
with my own hands.

227
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:34,194
I was just asking.

228
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:37,864
You were
criticizing<i> again.</i>

229
00:11:37,905 --> 00:11:40,534
Relax. She's not
going to reject

230
00:11:40,575 --> 00:11:41,784
a prospective daughter

231
00:11:41,826 --> 00:11:43,286
because the
<i>var'Hama</i> candles

232
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:44,787
in her welcoming
display were replicated.

233
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:45,913
(<i> door chimes</i> )

234
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,457
Come in.

235
00:11:52,671 --> 00:11:55,882
<i>Tug son bosh mok</i>
<i>A'Beh, Sirella koH.</i>

236
00:11:55,923 --> 00:11:57,384
<i>E'Gagh vet moh.</i>

237
00:11:58,301 --> 00:12:00,719
What is<i> he</i> doing here?

238
00:12:00,761 --> 00:12:02,763
I meant no disrespect.

239
00:12:02,805 --> 00:12:04,015
Then leave.

240
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:16,236
Your worthiness to join
our House will now be judged

241
00:12:16,277 --> 00:12:18,737
according to the traditions
of my family.

242
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:20,114
I am prepared, my lady.

243
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:21,949
I doubt that.

244
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:26,496
A Klingon woman would find it
difficult to gain my favor.

245
00:12:26,538 --> 00:12:29,165
For...an<i> alien,</i>

246
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:31,543
it will most likely
be impossible.

247
00:12:31,585 --> 00:12:33,086
I like a challenge.

248
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:37,716
I will not have my authority
challenged by you.

249
00:12:37,756 --> 00:12:39,467
That's not what I meant.

250
00:12:39,509 --> 00:12:42,845
If you cannot say
what you mean,
say nothing at all.

251
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:47,058
The evaluation
will begin tomorrow morning.

252
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:51,062
Have the traditional meal
prepared before I arrive.

253
00:12:52,813 --> 00:12:54,524
And in the future,

254
00:12:54,566 --> 00:12:58,403
