such obvious fakes.

256
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,550
You never told me
that your wife
was opposed to this marriage.

257
00:13:20,592 --> 00:13:22,636
Sirella is a woman
of strong convictions.

258
00:13:22,677 --> 00:13:24,512
She believes
that by bringing aliens

259
00:13:24,554 --> 00:13:27,223
into our families,
we risk losing our identity

260
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:28,516
as Klingons.

261
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:30,393
That is a prejudiced,
xenophobic view.

262
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,395
We<i> are</i> Klingons, Worf.

263
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:36,357
We don't<i> embrace</i>
other cultures.
We<i> conquer</i> them.

264
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:39,778
If someone wishes to join us,
they must honor our traditions

265
00:13:39,818 --> 00:13:41,446
and prove themselves worthy

266
00:13:41,488 --> 00:13:43,990
of wearing the crest
of a Great House.

267
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:45,492
Jadzia<i> is</i> worthy.

268
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,327
Of course she is.

269
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:50,497
She's an honorable woman
and a formidable warrior.

270
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:53,249
You should say<i> that</i> to Sirella.

271
00:13:54,334 --> 00:13:55,752
That's not such a good idea.

272
00:13:55,794 --> 00:13:57,878
I don't want her to think

273
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:02,342
that I'm interfering
in her domain.

274
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,552
Perhaps I should
speak with her.

275
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:07,472
Coming from me, it would
not seem like a challenge

276
00:14:07,514 --> 00:14:08,723
to her authority.

277
00:14:08,765 --> 00:14:10,725
I wouldn't do that
if I were you.

278
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:13,770
Why?

279
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:16,523
Well, um...

280
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:19,359
the truth is...

281
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,653
she doesn't like you
that much either.

282
00:14:21,695 --> 00:14:23,488
Me.

283
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,532
Don't let that
bother you.

284
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:28,493
I had every right
to bring you into the family

285
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:30,244
and she's accepted the fact

286
00:14:30,286 --> 00:14:33,039
that there's<i> nothing</i>
she can do about it.

287
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,499
How comforting.

288
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:36,751
(<i> chuckles</i> )

289
00:14:36,793 --> 00:14:40,004
(<i> laughing</i> )

290
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:43,800
And they say that
you have no sense of humor.

291
00:14:43,842 --> 00:14:47,303
(<i> laughing</i> )

292
00:15:01,067 --> 00:15:03,528
Phew. I could do
without the heat.

293
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:06,113
I can't, uh, say much
for the decor either.

294
00:15:06,155 --> 00:15:08,742
Well, it can't be
<i>all</i> fun and games.

295
00:15:08,783 --> 00:15:12,078
I'm sure there has to be
some sort of ritual

296
00:15:12,119 --> 00:15:15,081
we have to go through
before the party begins.

297
00:15:15,122 --> 00:15:18,251
There<i> is</i> going to be
a party, isn't there?

298
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:19,753
You're asking me?

299
00:15:19,794 --> 00:15:22,714
I can barely say
my name in Klingon.

300
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:25,759
MARTOK:
Prepare yourselves,
my friends

301
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,219
for a journey
you won't soon forget.

302
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,309
These...

303
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,853
are<i> Ma'Stakas.</i>

304
00:15:36,895 --> 00:15:38,688
What, uh, what do
we do with them?

305
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:41,190
At the conclusion
of the wedding ceremony

306
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:43,693
you will use them
to attack Worf and Dax.

307
00:15:43,735 --> 00:15:45,403
Obviously.
Don't you know anything?

308
00:15:45,445 --> 00:15:46,696
The tradition dates back

309
00:15:46,738 --> 00:15:48,740
to the wedding
of Kahless and Lukara

310
00:15:48,782 --> 00:15:50,533
who were nearly killed
by Molor's troops

311
00:15:50,575 --> 00:15:51,951
moments after they were
married.

312
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:53,661
Until the ceremony,

313
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:55,079
you should keep these with you
at all times.

314
00:15:55,121 --> 00:15:56,706
SISKO:
I trust

315
00:15:56,748 --> 00:15:59,292
this combat is non-lethal.

316
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,920
It is a symbolic
attack only.

317
00:16:01,961 --> 00:16:03,254
Oh.

318
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,717
That food is not
to be eaten.

319
00:16:09,051 --> 00:16:10,386
Then what is it for?

320
00:16:10,428 --> 00:16:13,389
It is there to tempt us
to break our fast.

321
00:16:13,431 --> 00:16:14,724
Fast?

322
00:16:14,766 --> 00:16:16,016
There are six trials

323
00:16:16,058 --> 00:16:18,603
we must face
on the path to<i> Kal'Hyah.</i>

324
00:16:18,645 --> 00:16:21,021
This is the first--
deprivation.

325
00:16:21,063 --> 00:16:23,274
We now begin a fast
that will continue

326
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:24,943
until the day of the wedding.

327
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,736
Well, th-that's
four days away.

328
00:16:26,778 --> 00:16:28,362
MARTOK:
It is a short time,

329
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,114
I know, but we must
make the best of it.

330
00:16:30,156 --> 00:16:33,326
What are
the other five trials?

331
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:36,996
Blood, pain, sacrifice,
anguish...

332
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:38,164
and death.

333
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:40,166
Sounds like marriage,
all right.

334
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,167
How would you know?

335
00:16:41,208 --> 00:16:43,002
It is time to begin.

336
00:16:48,341 --> 00:16:50,384
QUARK:
Need more flowers
on the banister.

337
00:16:50,426 --> 00:16:52,011
MALE:
We're ready
with the banner, boss.

338
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,346
(<i> whistles</i> )

339
00:16:53,387 --> 00:16:54,555
Raise it.

340
00:16:54,597 --> 00:16:56,265
You're up early.

341
00:16:56,307 --> 00:16:57,725
I thought writers
slept late.

342
00:16:57,767 --> 00:16:58,893
Not always.

343
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:00,687
I sold my first
book today.

344
00:17:00,728 --> 00:17:03,481
Really? How much
did you get for it?

345
00:17:03,523 --> 00:17:05,149
It's just a
figure of speech.

346
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,776
The Federation
News Service

347
00:17:06,818 --> 00:17:08,319
is going to publish
a book of my stories

348
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,737
about life on the station
under Dominion rule.

349
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:11,489
And they're not
paying you?

350
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:12,699
No.

351
00:17:12,740 --> 00:17:14,492
Well, then you have
my sympathies

352
00:17:14,534 --> 00:17:16,452
and the first round
of drinks is on the house.

353
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:17,578
Really?

354
00:17:17,620 --> 00:17:20,790
No. It's a figure
of speech.

355
00:17:20,832 --> 00:17:22,291
Look, I want to tell
my dad about the book.

356
00:17:22,333 --> 00:17:24,002
Is he still in
the holosuite?

357
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:26,963
Oh, yeah.
They're still up there.

358
00:17:27,005 --> 00:17:28,882
What are they doing?

359
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:31,509
It's a Klingon
bachelor party.

360
00:17:33,845 --> 00:17:35,054
You're a writer.

361
00:17:35,095 --> 00:17:37,181
Use your imagination.

362
00:17:39,726 --> 00:17:41,895
BASHIR:
Alexander.

363
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:44,898
Grandma?

364
00:17:44,939 --> 00:17:46,482
Guess again.

365
00:17:49,986 --> 00:17:51,320
We're still on the...?

366
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:55,449
The road to<i> Kal'Hyah,</i>
day 500.

367
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:57,577
Maybe we should
turn down the heat

368
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:59,453
you know, for
Alexander's sake.

369
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,789
Oh, no, it's okay.
I, uh...

370
00:18:01,831 --> 00:18:04,792
I just need some water.

371
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:07,712
Now, you don't want
to push yourself too hard.

372
00:18:07,754 --> 00:18:11,549
You know, turning down the heat
might be a good idea.

373
00:18:12,383 --> 00:18:14,552
The whole point
is to push yourself

374
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:17,513
to the limits
of your endurance.

375
00:18:18,890 --> 00:18:21,100
(<i> panting</i> )

376
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:23,728
I will.

377
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:27,147
I want to travel
the entire path to<i> Kal'Hyah.</i>

378
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:29,400
Stoke the fire again!

379
00:18:29,442 --> 00:18:31,318
As you wish.

380
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:37,241
Of course, we cannot expect
you non-Klingons to...

381
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:39,702
have the same stamina
as we do.

382
00:18:39,744 --> 00:18:42,204
If you wish to quit,
no one will think

383
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:43,497
any less of you.

384
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:45,249
Who said anything
about quitting?

385
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:47,167
Not me.

386
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:49,378
I like the heat.

387
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:51,714
That's the spirit.

388
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:55,342
