<i>t'lang</i>

397
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:15,989
<i>cho.</i>

398
00:19:19,283 --> 00:19:20,701
Again.

399
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:23,913
I've done it
three times already.

400
00:19:23,955 --> 00:19:26,833
You continue
to rush through
the ceremony,

401
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:29,502
your body
position is poor,

402
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,504
and the placement
of the braziers

403
00:19:31,545 --> 00:19:34,674
on their pedestals
is sloppy.

404
00:19:37,551 --> 00:19:40,471
Do you know how heavy
those things are?

405
00:19:40,513 --> 00:19:43,223
A Klingon woman
would not complain.

406
00:19:43,265 --> 00:19:45,476
You wouldn't make
a Klingon woman

407
00:19:45,518 --> 00:19:46,644
do it three times in a row.

408
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,146
I wouldn't have to.

409
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,439
She'd have done it correctly
the first time.

410
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:55,820
End this now, Jadzia.

411
00:19:55,862 --> 00:19:58,197
Go back to your own people.

412
00:19:58,238 --> 00:20:00,658
They will tolerate
your weaknesses

413
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:03,786
and your failings
in a way that
a Klingon family

414
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:05,412
never will.

415
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:09,167
In our House, you would
always be an alien--

416
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:11,293
an outsider.

417
00:20:11,335 --> 00:20:12,879
At best, you'd be
an object of pity

418
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,297
but you'd never
be accepted

419
00:20:15,339 --> 00:20:16,757
never an equal

420
00:20:16,799 --> 00:20:20,553
because you can never
truly be one of us.

421
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:30,104
<i>Ko'ma tlang'goS ak-bay</i>

422
