Now begins
the Trial of Blood.

486
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:43,381
MARTOK:
Let rivers flow from our veins.

487
00:23:43,421 --> 00:23:45,174
Who will be first?

488
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,894
I did not expect it
to be you, Doctor.

489
00:23:59,272 --> 00:24:00,731
Neither did I.

490
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:02,024
Do not worry.

491
00:24:02,066 --> 00:24:04,902
The pain will last
for only a moment.

492
00:24:12,450 --> 00:24:14,078
Ta-hoo!

493
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:17,373
(<i> loud, rapid drumming</i> )

494
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,431
Isn't that grand?

495
00:24:33,471 --> 00:24:35,808
Yeah! Whoo!

496
00:24:37,393 --> 00:24:39,395
(<i> applause and cheering</i> )

497
00:24:39,437 --> 00:24:40,938
All right!
He's unbelievable.

498
00:24:40,980 --> 00:24:42,522
He's something.

499
00:24:46,235 --> 00:24:48,362
Lieutenant Manuele Atoa

500
00:24:48,404 --> 00:24:50,323
from the Starship
<i>Sutherland.</i>

501
00:24:50,364 --> 00:24:52,116
I've never seen
anything like that.

502
00:24:52,158 --> 00:24:54,327
Neither have I.

503
00:24:57,371 --> 00:24:58,789
Let's get something to eat.

504
00:25:00,958 --> 00:25:02,960
A woman of many talents.

505
00:25:03,002 --> 00:25:05,045
It's a shame
she's about to waste them all

506
00:25:05,087 --> 00:25:08,674
on that walking frown
she calls a fiancé.

507
00:25:08,715 --> 00:25:10,092
She's too good for him.

508
00:25:10,134 --> 00:25:11,302
I've said that
from the beginning.

509
00:25:11,344 --> 00:25:13,053
Are you jealous?

510
00:25:14,430 --> 00:25:16,307
There's no profit
in jealousy.

511
00:25:16,349 --> 00:25:18,642
That's not a denial.

512
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:23,230
It's not to be
quoted either.

513
00:25:23,272 --> 00:25:24,315
Oh, don't worry.

514
00:25:24,357 --> 00:25:25,774
So when did
you first realize

515
00:25:25,816 --> 00:25:27,443
you had these
feelings for Dax?

516
00:25:28,235 --> 00:25:29,778
Quark, wait.

517
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:38,371
Miles?

518
00:25:38,412 --> 00:25:39,997
Yeah?

519
00:25:40,039 --> 00:25:43,209
It's working.

520
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:45,002
I've had a vision...

521
00:25:45,044 --> 00:25:46,837
about the future.

522
00:25:46,879 --> 00:25:49,715
I can see it so clearly.

523
00:25:51,300 --> 00:25:52,801
What is it?

524
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:57,764
I'm going to kill Worf.

525
00:25:59,350 --> 00:26:01,227
I'm going to kill Worf.

526
00:26:01,268 --> 00:26:03,729
That's what I'm going to do.

527
00:26:03,770 --> 00:26:05,731
I can see it clearly now.

528
00:26:05,772 --> 00:26:07,607
I'm going to kill him.

529
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:09,151
Kill Worf.

530
00:26:09,193 --> 00:26:10,486
Kill Worf.

531
00:26:10,528 --> 00:26:11,529
Kill Worf.

532
00:26:11,569 --> 00:26:12,738
Kill Worf.

533
00:26:12,779 --> 00:26:13,739
(<i> coughs</i> )

534
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:15,324
Kill Worf.

535
00:26:15,366 --> 00:26:18,077
(<i> loud drumming and</i>
<i>conversations continue</i> )

536
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:37,012
I've been getting complaints
about the noise.

537
00:26:37,054 --> 00:26:39,265
Someone even
mentioned a fight?

538
00:26:39,306 --> 00:26:41,183
Oh, there was a scuffle

539
00:26:41,225 --> 00:26:43,685
between Morn
and one of the Bolians

540
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:45,438
but they
worked it out.

541
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:47,523
How long will this...

542
00:26:47,565 --> 00:26:49,442
party continue?

543
00:26:49,483 --> 00:26:53,153
This party will continue
until further notice

544
00:26:53,195 --> 00:26:55,739
on the personal
authority

545
00:26:55,781 --> 00:26:57,241
of this station's
First Officer

546
00:26:57,283 --> 00:26:58,451
who just happens
to be me.

547
00:26:58,492 --> 00:26:59,826
Mm-hmm.

548
00:26:59,868 --> 00:27:01,495
You're in a good mood.

549
00:27:01,537 --> 00:27:04,123
Well, it's
a good party.

550
00:27:04,998 --> 00:27:06,375
Well...

551
00:27:06,417 --> 00:27:07,793
Odo...

552
00:27:08,835 --> 00:27:10,796
Odo...

553
00:27:10,837 --> 00:27:13,757
I think we have
a lot to talk about.

554
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:15,801
I agree.

555
00:27:15,842 --> 00:27:17,595
So let's talk.

556
00:27:17,635 --> 00:27:19,346
Now?

557
00:27:19,388 --> 00:27:21,807
Don't you think we've
put it off long enough?

558
00:27:24,143 --> 00:27:25,894
Enjoy yourselves.

559
00:27:27,354 --> 00:27:29,356
Let's, um...

560
00:27:29,398 --> 00:27:31,400
find someplace
a little quieter.

561
00:27:34,820 --> 00:27:37,906
(<i> yells</i> )

562
00:27:40,951 --> 00:27:42,620
Thanks for the show.

563
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:45,289
Thanks for getting me
the day off.

564
00:27:45,331 --> 00:27:46,748
Captain Shelby
owed me a favor.

565
00:27:46,790 --> 00:27:48,208
Actually,
owed me several.

566
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:50,877
In fact, how would
you like to have

567
00:27:50,919 --> 00:27:52,546
another two days off?

568
00:27:52,588 --> 00:27:54,214
Two?

569
00:27:54,256 --> 00:27:55,508
What do I have to do?

570
00:27:55,549 --> 00:27:56,842
Not much.

571
00:27:56,883 --> 00:27:58,718
Just give me something
fun to look at

572
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,429
for the rest
of the evening.

573
00:28:00,471 --> 00:28:01,347
Anything else?

574
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:03,641
I'll let you know.

575
00:28:03,681 --> 00:28:05,309
SIRELLA:
You!

576
00:28:06,684 --> 00:28:09,146
Leave her
or I'll cut your head off

577
00:28:09,188 --> 00:28:10,688
and hang it from my belt.

578
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:12,316
I'll take care of this.

579
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:14,734
(<i> drumming and conversations</i>
<i>stop</i> )

580
00:28:14,776 --> 00:28:16,028
You weren't invited.

581
00:28:16,069 --> 00:28:18,989
It is time
for the<i> Bre'Nan</i> ritual.

582
00:28:19,031 --> 00:28:20,616
I'm busy.

583
00:28:20,658 --> 00:28:24,411
Busy acting
like a Risian slut.

584
00:28:25,371 --> 00:28:28,040
I'm only going to ask
you to leave once.

585
00:28:28,081 --> 00:28:30,209
You will come
with me now and perform

586
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:32,586
the<i> Bre'Nan</i> ritual
to my satisfaction

587
00:28:32,628 --> 00:28:34,796
or I will cancel your wedding.

588
00:28:34,838 --> 00:28:36,382
<i>Toruk-DOH!</i>

589
00:28:38,884 --> 00:28:40,135
NOG:
Ladies, please.

590
00:28:40,177 --> 00:28:42,054
SIRELLA:
<i>Mok'Ta vor</i>

591
00:28:42,095 --> 00:28:43,972
<i>kash a'VEH!</i>

592
00:28:50,688 --> 00:28:52,814
Why is everyone
standing around?

593
00:28:52,856 --> 00:28:55,108
The party's
just getting started.

594
00:28:55,150 --> 00:28:56,652
Play something!

595
00:28:56,694 --> 00:28:58,862
(<i> drumming resumes</i> )

596
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:17,381
Double<i> raktajino,</i> extra sweet.

597
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:21,594
(<i> groans</i> )

598
00:29:21,635 --> 00:29:23,679
What time is it?

599
00:29:23,721 --> 00:29:25,389
1030 hours.

600
00:29:26,557 --> 00:29:28,016
Come on.

601
00:29:31,395 --> 00:29:33,606
Wrong door.

602
00:29:39,945 --> 00:29:41,947
Excuse me, sir.

603
00:29:50,830 --> 00:29:51,790
Jadzia

604
00:29:51,831 --> 00:29:54,000
we need to...

605
00:29:57,087 --> 00:29:58,631
You're mad.

606
00:29:58,672 --> 00:30:01,467
I am concerned.

607
00:30:01,508 --> 00:30:03,552
Yeah, well, I'm hung over.

608
00:30:03,594 --> 00:30:05,137
Can we talk later?

609
00:30:05,178 --> 00:30:07,681
We have a very
serious problem.

610
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:10,225
Sirella has canceled
the wedding.

611
00:30:10,267 --> 00:30:13,186
She doesn't waste
any time, does she?

612
00:30:13,228 --> 00:30:15,439
She said
you attacked her.

613
00:30:16,649 --> 00:30:18,776
She pulled a knife.

614
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:25,865
You are forbidden to join
the House of Martok.

615
00:30:25,907 --> 00:30:28,661
So I won't be invited
to the family picnics.

616
00:30:28,702 --> 00:30:30,496
I'll live.

617
00:30:30,537 --> 00:30:33,415
I cannot believe
how you're taking
this so lightly.

618
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:34,667
Do you hear that?

619
00:30:34,708 --> 00:30:36,084
What?

620
00:30:36,126 --> 00:30:37,628
(<i> muffled voices</i> )

621
00:30:37,670 --> 00:30:39,630
It sounds like voices.

622
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:46,679
Hi.
Hi.

623
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:48,930
ODO:
Is the party over?

624
00:30:48,972 --> 00:30:52,392
You could say that.
It's 10:30.

625
00:30:52,434 --> 00:30:55,103
In the morning?
I'm on duty.

626
00:30:55,145 --> 00:30:56,730
So am I.

627
00:30:56,772 --> 00:30:57,856
It was a great party.

628
00:30:57,897 --> 00:30:59,274
Thanks.

629
00:31:06,156 --> 00:31:08,158
We must deal
with the situation now.

630
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:11,745
Stop yelling.
My head hurts.

631
00:31:11,787 --> 00:31:15,123
You must go to Sirella
and beg her forgiveness.

632
00:31:22,172 --> 00:31:24,007
I don't beg.

633
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:27,720
You are allowing
your pride to blind you.

634
00:31:27,761 --> 00:31:29,179
Look who's talking.

635
00:31:29,221 --> 00:31:31,139
You want me to go crawling
to some old hag

636
00:31:31,181 --> 00:31:33,308
just so you can have your
traditional Klingon wedding.

637
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:36,144
This is about more
than just tradition.

638
00:31:38,313 --> 00:31:41,734
You and I have embarked
on a spiritual journey,

639
00:31:41,775 --> 00:31:43,276
one that will
bind us together

640
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:45,487
through this life
and into the next.

641
00:31:45,529 --> 00:31:47,113
You cannot turn back now.

642
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:49,742
Maybe you're on
a spiritual journey, Worf,

643
00:31:49,783 --> 00:31:51,869
but I just want
to get married.

644
00:31:51,910 --> 00:31:55,497
So why don't you go back
to sweating and bleeding

645
00:31:55,539 --> 00:31:57,416
with your friends
in the holosuite,

646
00:31:57,457 --> 00:31:58,792
and when you're done,

647
00:31:58,834 --> 00:32:00,586
meet me in
Benjamin's office

648
00:32:00,627 --> 00:32:02,546
and he'll perform
the ceremony.

649
00:32:10,679 --> 00:32:12,890
If that is your attitude...

650
00:32:15,141 --> 00:32:17,436
perhaps Sirella
was right about you.

651
00:32:20,564 --> 00:32:23,066
There should be no wedding.

652
00:32:24,192 --> 00:32:26,111
That's fine with me.

653
00:32:28,822 --> 00:32:31,241
(<i> door opens, closes</i> )

654
00:32:45,589 --> 00:32:49,802
(<i> whistling</i> )

655
00:32:49,843 --> 00:32:51,219
What's going on?

656
00:32:51,261 --> 00:32:52,304
Haven't you heard?

657
00:32:52,345 --> 00:32:53,430
The wedding's off.

658
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:55,181
Off? Why?

659
00:32:55,223 --> 00:33:00,061
She says it's because
he's a pig-headed, stubborn man

660
00:33:00,103 --> 00:33:02,606
who puts tradition
before everything else.

661
00:33:02,648 --> 00:33:05,150
He says it's because
she's a frivolous

662
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:06,693
emotional woman

663
00:33:06,735 --> 00:33:09,154
who refuses to take him
or his culture seriously.

664
00:33:09,195 --> 00:33:11,490
You can see
the problem.

665
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:13,116
They're both right.

666
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:14,409
Exactly.

667
00:33:14,451 --> 00:33:17,871
Well... there's only
one thing for it.

668
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:21,166
Dinner.

669
00:33:21,207 --> 00:33:23,418
I'll get the menu.

670
00:33:31,343 --> 00:33:33,011
(<i> door chimes</i> )

671
00:33:33,052 --> 00:33:34,513
Enter.

672
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,730
Worf...

673
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:46,024
you've made a grave error.

674
00:33:48,067 --> 00:33:50,904
Perhaps.

675
00:33:50,946 --> 00:33:53,239
Do you still love her?

676
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:55,283
Of course.

677
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:58,411
However, in this
case,<i> that...</i>

678
00:33:58,453 --> 00:34:00,580
may not be enough.

679
00:34:02,499 --> 00:34:05,544
Anyone can see that we are
hopelessly mismatched.

680
00:34:05,585 --> 00:34:07,796
She is a Trill;
I am a Klingon.

681
00:34:07,838 --> 00:34:10,632
She has had
five marriages.

682
00:34:10,674 --> 00:34:12,843
This would be my first.

683
00:34:12,885 --> 00:34:15,929
When she is laughing,
I am somber.

684
00:34:15,971 --> 00:34:17,723
When I am happy,
she is crying.

685
00:34:17,764 --> 00:34:21,059
She plays<i> tongo</i> with
the Ferengi bartender.

686
00:34:21,100 --> 00:34:23,395
I can barely stand him.

687
00:34:25,564 --> 00:34:28,400
She mocks everything...

688
00:34:28,441 --> 00:34:31,152
while I take
everything seriously.

689
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:36,491
She is nothing
like the woman
I thought I would marry.

690
00:34:38,827 --> 00:34:41,204
We are not accorded
the luxury

691
00:34:41,246 --> 00:34:44,750
of choosing the women
we fall in love with.

692
00:34:44,791 --> 00:34:47,711
Do you think Sirella
is anything like the woman

693
00:34:47,753 --> 00:34:49,880
I thought that I'd marry?

694
00:34:51,339 --> 00:34:56,302
She is a prideful,
arrogant, mercurial woman

695
00:34:56,344 --> 00:35:01,224
who shares my bed far too
infrequently for my taste.

696
00:35:02,392 --> 00:35:04,394
And yet...

697
00:35:05,979 --> 00:35:08,314
I love her...

698
00:35:08,356 --> 00:35:10,400
deeply.

699
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:12,360
Hmm.

700
00:35:12,402 --> 00:35:16,823
We Klingons often tout our...

701
00:35:16,865 --> 00:35:18,951
prowess in battle...

702
00:35:18,992 --> 00:35:24,289
our desire for glory and honor
above all else...

703
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:27,751
but how hollow is
the sound of victory...

704
00:35:27,793 --> 00:35:30,879
without someone
to share it with?

705
00:35:30,921 --> 00:35:34,091
Honor gives
little comfort

706
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:36,259
to a man alone
in his home...

707
00:35:36,301 --> 00:35:39,054
and in his heart.

708
00:35:44,726 --> 00:35:46,352
One steak with mushrooms

709
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:48,187
baked potato, sour cream
and chives.

710
00:35:48,229 --> 00:35:49,606
I should have had that.

711
00:35:49,648 --> 00:35:53,026
One double Altair sandwich,
no mustard...

712
00:35:53,068 --> 00:35:54,820
two bowls of linguini,

713
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:57,948
Bajoran shrimp
with extra cheese.

714
00:35:57,990 --> 00:36:00,408
One loaf of mapa bread.

715
00:36:00,450 --> 00:36:02,368
Quark, where's
the<i> kava</i> juice?

716
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:03,662
They're still
squeezing the roots

717
00:36:03,703 --> 00:36:05,204
unless you want replicated.

718
00:36:05,246 --> 00:36:06,581
We'll wait.

719
00:36:06,623 --> 00:36:08,583
SISKO:
What do you think
you're doing?

720
00:36:09,626 --> 00:36:10,794
The wedding's
been called off.

721
00:36:10,836 --> 00:36:11,920
It's back on.

722
00:36:11,962 --> 00:36:14,589
Worf is apologizing
to Jadzia

723
00:36:14,631 --> 00:36:15,924
at this very moment.

724
00:36:15,966 --> 00:36:17,509
Quark, take
it all away.

725
00:36:17,550 --> 00:36:20,261
No food for those
on the path to<i> Kal'Hyah.</i>

726
00:36:20,303 --> 00:36:23,473
No refunds for those
on the path
to<i> Kal'Hyah</i> as well.

727
00:36:23,515 --> 00:36:24,766
Sorry.

728
00:36:29,646 --> 00:36:32,024
Father, what happened?

729
00:36:34,317 --> 00:36:36,277
She refused
to change her mind

730
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:38,363
and the wedding is still off.

731
00:36:38,404 --> 00:36:39,656
(<i> sighs</i> )

732
00:36:39,698 --> 00:36:40,824
Where is she?

733
00:36:40,866 --> 00:36:42,826
In her quarters.

734
00:36:42,868 --> 00:36:44,953
I'll go talk to her.

735
00:36:44,995 --> 00:36:48,456
Just... keep them away
from the food?

736
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:56,589
(<i> door chimes</i> )

737
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:57,966
Come in!

738
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:00,969
Save your breath.

739
00:37:01,011 --> 00:37:03,262
Worf's gone too far,
and now it's over.

740
00:37:03,304 --> 00:37:05,306
Do you know what
he wanted me to do?

741
00:37:05,348 --> 00:37:08,768
He wanted me to go crawling
on my hands and knees
to Sirella

742
00:37:08,810 --> 00:37:10,353
to beg her forgiveness.

743
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:11,813
Beg her! Me!

744
00:37:11,855 --> 00:37:13,523
I was once

745
00:37:13,565 --> 00:37:16,860
the Federation Ambassador
to the Klingon Empire.

746
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:20,780
I negotiated
the Khitomer Accords

747
00:37:20,822 --> 00:37:22,407
before Worf
was even born.

748
00:37:22,448 --> 00:37:24,450
Curzonnegotiated the Accords!

749
00:37:24,492 --> 00:37:25,994
And I've got news for you,
old man.

750
00:37:26,036 --> 00:37:27,662
You're not Curzon anymore.

751
00:37:27,704 --> 00:37:30,082
And what the hell is that
supposed to mean?

752
00:37:30,123 --> 00:37:32,042
It means that you
can't expect Sirella

753
00:37:32,084 --> 00:37:33,292
to treat you like Curzon

754
00:37:33,334 --> 00:37:35,670
just because you carry
his memories.

755
00:37:35,712 --> 00:37:37,172
To her, you're just
a young woman

756
00:37:37,214 --> 00:37:39,465
who decided to marry
into her family.

757
00:37:39,507 --> 00:37:41,051
If it means
you have to bow down

758
00:37:41,093 --> 00:37:42,677
and kiss her boots,

759
00:37:42,719 --> 00:37:45,972
that's exactly what you have
to do, and you knew that.

760
00:37:46,014 --> 00:37:48,349
The moment you decided
to marry Worf,

761
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:50,643
you knew that sooner or later
you'd have to bow down

762
00:37:50,685 --> 00:37:53,354
and show her the respect
that she's due.

763
00:37:53,396 --> 00:37:55,023
This is Worf's fault--

764
00:37:55,065 --> 00:37:57,650
Worf and his traditional
Klingon wedding.

765
00:37:57,692 --> 00:37:59,945
Well, he may have let
this wedding business

766
00:37:59,986 --> 00:38:04,116
go to his head,
but you are 356 years old.

767
00:38:04,157 --> 00:38:07,077
Compared to you,
Worf is just a kid.

768
00:38:07,119 --> 00:38:10,205
And if you can't abide
by Klingon traditions,

769
00:38:10,247 --> 00:38:11,748
then you never should
have let yourself

770
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:14,500
fall in love with him
in the first place.

771
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:19,714
And you<i> are</i>
in love with him.

772
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:24,136
I wasn't looking
to fall in love.

773
00:38:24,177 --> 00:38:27,346
I was perfectly happy
by myself.

774
00:38:27,388 --> 00:38:30,850
I had friends, a career,
adventure...

775
00:38:33,519 --> 00:38:36,773
Then one day...

776
00:38:36,815 --> 00:38:39,609
this Klingon
with a bad attitude

777
00:38:39,651 --> 00:38:41,153
walked into my life

778
00:38:41,194 --> 00:38:45,490
and the next thing I know,
I'm getting married.

779
00:38:45,531 --> 00:38:49,661
After 356 years
and seven lifetimes...

780
00:38:51,204 --> 00:38:53,581
I still lead with my heart.

781
00:38:53,623 --> 00:38:57,376
You know, that is
what I've always
loved about you.

782
00:39:00,088 --> 00:39:03,049
And I think that's why
Worf loves you, too.

783
00:39:08,888 --> 00:39:11,933
(<i> sighs</i> )

784
00:39:11,975 --> 00:39:18,606
Whatever happened to that
young, callow Ensign
I used to know?

785
00:39:18,648 --> 00:39:21,193
The one who used
to turn to me

786
00:39:21,234 --> 00:39:23,361
for advice all the time?

787
00:39:23,402 --> 00:39:27,365
You know,
the one with hair?

788
00:39:27,406 --> 00:39:29,492
I grew up.

789
00:39:33,538 --> 00:39:36,624
I guess it's time
I grow up, too.

790
00:39:36,666 --> 00:39:38,751
Mmm.

791
00:40:19,334 --> 00:40:21,586
With fire and steel

792
00:40:21,627 --> 00:40:25,215
did the gods forge
the Klingon heart.

793
00:40:25,257 --> 00:40:27,008
So fiercely did it beat,

794
00:40:27,050 --> 00:40:30,887
so loud was the sound,
that the gods cried out,

795
00:40:30,929 --> 00:40:33,973
"On this day
we have brought forth

796
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:37,685
"the strongest heart
in all the heavens.

797
00:40:37,727 --> 00:40:41,189
"None can stand before it
without trembling

798
00:40:41,231 --> 00:40:42,648
at its strength."

799
00:40:42,690 --> 00:40:46,152
But then the Klingon heart
weakened

800
00:40:46,194 --> 00:40:48,821
its steady rhythm faltered
and the gods said,

801
00:40:48,863 --> 00:40:51,116
"Why have you weakened so?

802
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:52,658
"We have made you the strongest

803
00:40:52,700 --> 00:40:55,661
in all of creation."

804
00:40:55,703 --> 00:40:57,580
And the heart said...

805
00:40:57,622 --> 00:40:58,915
I am alone.

806
00:41:00,792 --> 00:41:03,044
And the gods knew
that they had erred.

807
00:41:03,086 --> 00:41:04,879
So they went back
to their forge

808
00:41:04,921 --> 00:41:08,216
and brought forth...
another heart.

809
00:41:37,287 --> 00:41:41,707
But the second heart
beat stronger than the first,

810
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:44,043
and the first was jealous
of its power.

811
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,633
Fortunately...

812
00:41:50,675 --> 00:41:52,218
the second heart
was tempered

813
00:41:52,260 --> 00:41:53,678
by wisdom.

814
00:41:53,719 --> 00:41:57,765
If we join together,
no force can stop us.

815
00:42:04,939 --> 00:42:08,318
And when the two hearts
began to beat together,

816
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:12,322
they filled the heavens
with a terrible sound.

817
00:42:12,364 --> 00:42:16,368
For the first time,
the gods knew fear.

818
00:42:16,409 --> 00:42:19,371
They tried to flee,
but it was too late.

819
00:42:19,412 --> 00:42:22,665
The Klingon hearts
destroyed the gods

820
00:42:22,707 --> 00:42:23,875
who created them

821
00:42:23,916 --> 00:42:27,253
and turned the heavens
to ashes.

822
00:42:27,295 --> 00:42:28,963
To this very day

823
00:42:29,005 --> 00:42:34,093
no one can oppose the beating
of two Klingon hearts.

824
00:42:36,595 --> 00:42:38,139
Not even me.

825
00:42:42,268 --> 00:42:46,523
Worf, son of Mogh,
does your heart beat

826
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:48,774
only for this woman?

827
00:42:48,816 --> 00:42:50,860
Yes.

828
00:42:50,902 --> 00:42:53,821
And will you swear
to join with her

829
00:42:53,863 --> 00:42:57,242
and stand with her
against all
who oppose you?

830
00:42:57,283 --> 00:42:59,869
I swear.

831
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:02,497
Jadzia, daughter of Kela,

832
00:43:02,539 --> 00:43:06,459
does your heart beat
only for this man?

833
00:43:06,501 --> 00:43:08,503
Yes.

834
00:43:08,545 --> 00:43:10,755
And do you swear
to join with him

835
00:43:10,796 --> 00:43:12,048
and stand with him

836
00:43:12,090 --> 00:43:13,883
against all
who would oppose you?

837
00:43:15,134 --> 00:43:17,011
(<i> whispering</i> ):
I swear.

838
00:43:18,096 --> 00:43:20,639
Then let all present
here today know

839
00:43:20,681 --> 00:43:25,437
that this man
and this woman are married.

840
00:43:25,478 --> 00:43:27,980
(<i> applause</i> )

841
00:43:33,278 --> 00:43:34,779
Now?

842
00:43:34,820 --> 00:43:36,531
Not yet.

843
00:43:43,913 --> 00:43:44,872
Now?

844
00:43:44,914 --> 00:43:46,999
Patience.

845
00:43:49,001 --> 00:43:50,628
My Lady.

846
00:43:52,004 --> 00:43:54,424
Welcome to the House
of Martok...

847
00:43:55,841 --> 00:43:57,718
my daughter.

848
00:44:02,098 --> 00:44:03,600
Now, Doctor!

849
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:06,561
(<i> yelling</i> )
